<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1435,1447,1615]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Geographical distribution: 
<collectingCountry box="[504,572,1484,1508]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[630,745,1484,1508]" name="Argentina" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. This species was described from “La Plata,” but if 
<bibRefCitation author="Hungerford" firstAuthor="Hungerford" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="23 - 27" refId="ref38143" refString="Hungerford, H. B. (1930) Three new Velia from South America. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 3, 23 - 27." type="journal article" year="1930">Hungerford (1930)</bibRefCitation>
was referring the city in 
<collectingCountry box="[568,682,1519,1543]" name="Argentina" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, the record is dubious, because no other specimens have been collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[253,510,1556,1580]" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Buenos Aires province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mazzucconi" box="[525,731,1556,1580]" firstAuthor="Mazzucconi" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="129 - 137" refId="ref39653" refString="Mazzucconi, S. A. (2000) Paravelia anta sp. n. and P. hungerfordi (Drake and Harris) from South America (Heteroptera: Veliidae). Aquatic Insects, 22, 129 - 137." type="journal article" year="2000">Mazzucconi 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
